<h2>What this is</h2>
<p>You will write a <strong>4-page policy brief</strong> on one Chennai-area climate-adaptation challenge for a hypothetical <strong>Greater Chennai Corporation</strong> planning audience. Same GCC audience you wrote for in the <a href="/units/unit-2/assessment-landscape-reading/">Landscape Reading</a> — but now you're operating in policy-brief format, with abstract climate science as the evidence base and concrete adaptation recommendations as the deliverable.</p>
<p>The Brief is defended in a live <strong>Policy Panel</strong> — 4-minute pitch + 3-minute Q&amp;A, with peers playing GCC officials asking cost, feasibility, equity, and science-credibility questions. Higher-stakes defense format than the U2 share-out.</p>

<h2>GRASPS framing (short version)</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Goal</strong>: Produce a 4-page policy brief on one climate-adaptation challenge for the Greater Chennai Corporation.</li>
  <li><strong>Role</strong>: Scientific advisor to GCC.</li>
  <li><strong>Audience</strong>: Hypothetical GCC officials + peer classmates (Policy Panel).</li>
  <li><strong>Situation</strong>: GCC has limited resources and faces multiple stressors. They need actionable, evidence-anchored, audience-appropriate recommendations.</li>
  <li><strong>Product</strong>: ≤4-page written brief OR ≤6-min video OR large infographic (same rubric).</li>
  <li><strong>Standards</strong>: HS-ESS3-5, HS-ESS3-6 primary. SEP-2 (model interpretation), SEP-4 (data interpretation), SEP-7 (argumentation), SEP-8 (communication).</li>
</ul>

<h2>Three deliverable formats — same rubric</h2>
<div class="callout">
  <div class="callout-title">Choose one format</div>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Written brief</strong> — ≤4 pages. Standard policy-brief structure: Executive Summary (1 page) · Background · Evidence + Projected Impacts · Recommendations · Sources.</li>
    <li><strong>Annotated video brief</strong> — ≤6 min, fully captioned. Screen-record yourself walking through the brief structure with visuals.</li>
    <li><strong>Large infographic</strong> — single visual with all 5 brief sections visible. Print-quality. Canva, Adobe Express, or Google Drawings.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Same rubric, same expectations. Format choice locked with Mr. Ignash by Block 11.</p>
</div>

<h2>The 8 adaptation challenges</h2>
<p>Pick one. The challenges span Chennai-specific climate impacts and span the year-arc — most connect forward to U5 (Hydrosphere), U6 (Biosphere + Land Use), or U7 (Energy). Picking a challenge that ties into the unit you're most curious about is allowed and encouraged.</p>

